Sunday Nwakanma, Umuahia Armey  checkpoints on Abia roads have disappeared. Our correspondent learnt that the  disappearance might  not be unconnected with the recent killing of a motorcyclist in Obingwa by a soldier at a military checkpoint in Ohanze. In Umuahia area, it was observed that the checkpoint close to Umuahia South LGA headquarters, the one at Atta Ibeku, as well as  the ones  along Umuahia-Uzuakoli-Ohafia road and Umuahia-Bende-Ohafia road had disappeared. A motorist, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said motorists in the state were happy with the development. Efforts to get the Army 14 Brigade, Ohafia,  for  comment was not successful as the Army Public Relations Officer was said to be on transferred.  Copyright PUNCH.
